description: Latin pustulatus, past participle of pustulare (“to blister”).

adjectives.description: pustulate (comparative more pustulate, superlative most pustulate)

entries.meaning: Having pustules or prominences resembling them.
examples: a pustulate leaf, shell, or coral

verbs.description: pustulate (third-person singular simple present pustulates, present participle pustulating, simple past and past participle pustulated)

entries.meaning: To form, or be formed into pustules
